


Pay n Save was the original drug store tenant in the University Mall, after Lawrences Department Store departed.  Pay n Save was a major drugstore chain based in Seattle, Washington.  In 1986, The company was was sold to the Thrifty Corporation, who later sold the stores to PayLess Drug, who retired the Pay n Save name.  Rite Aid then bought Thrifty Payless Holdings, Inc. in 1998.  The Davis Pay n Save location became a Payless, then a Rite Aid.  Rite Aid moved across the street when the Mall was remodeled In 1999. In 2000, the space became a Gottschalks, and is now currently a Forever 21.

